WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:04.155
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:04.696 --> 00:18.376
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:19.117 --> 00:26.688
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:26.708 --> 00:27.890
Today,

00:27.970 --> 00:35.998
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:40.543 --> 00:41.163
Peace be with you.

00:41.384 --> 00:47.089
Friends, we come to this great feast of the Holy Family, which follows immediately upon Christmas.

00:47.690 --> 00:50.593
And I think that Chuck's position itself is very interesting.

00:50.653 --> 00:55.698
So the first Sunday after Christmas, the church wants us to think about

00:55.938 --> 00:56.739
the Holy Family.

00:57.160 --> 00:59.363
Now take it out of a merely sentimental context.

00:59.403 --> 01:01.306
I think there's a deeper theological reason.

01:02.347 --> 01:03.369
The child has come.

01:04.190 --> 01:11.881
So the Christ child, the son of God, the Savior, but who comes as a little baby who therefore requires what?

01:13.182 --> 01:16.227
The protection and nurturance of a family.

01:17.108 --> 01:24.178
We're asked to think right away about those figures, Mary Joseph, who surround and protect this child.

01:24.322 --> 01:32.011
Now this will be of great spiritual significance for us because Christmas, as you know, is finally about the birth of Christ in us.

01:33.252 --> 01:37.417
So what do we need to protect that Christ child being born in us?

01:37.517 --> 01:40.160
I think that's what this juxtaposition is about.

01:41.020 --> 01:50.291
So what I wanna do is make a really explicit connection to Christmas, but especially with this idea of the child that requires protection.

01:51.092 --> 01:53.234
Now to do this, I'm gonna draw attention.

01:53.922 --> 02:02.153
to a little thought about, but fourth telling of the Christmas story in the New Testament.

02:02.173 --> 02:05.478
In St. John, we have the austerely metaphysical account, right?

02:05.498 --> 02:07.440
The word became flesh and dwelt among us.

02:07.580 --> 02:08.301
Okay, we know that.

02:09.002 --> 02:13.228
Then we know the two historical narrative accounts in Matthew and Luke.

02:13.909 --> 02:17.714
So Matthew's account has the star and has the magi and

02:17.794 --> 02:24.461
has the massacre of the innocents, Luke's account is distinctive because it has the senses and the stable and the shepherds and the angels.

02:25.222 --> 02:29.447
Usually when we think about Christmas and we kind of mash together of Matthew and Luke.

02:30.088 --> 02:32.370
But we have those three more familiar accounts.

02:33.391 --> 02:34.593
But then there's a fourth one.

02:35.934 --> 02:39.558
It's found in the 12th chapter of the book of Revelation.

02:40.419 --> 02:41.621
You say the book of Revelation.

02:41.681 --> 02:42.662
How's that about Christmas?

02:42.762 --> 02:46.386
Well, look how the 12th chapter of Revelation begins.

02:47.554 --> 02:50.798
A great portent appeared in heaven.

02:51.660 --> 02:58.809
A woman closed with the sun, with the moon under her feet, and on her head, a crown of 12 stars.

02:59.490 --> 03:00.171
Well, who is this?

03:01.273 --> 03:03.155
People read her as symbolic of Israel and so on.

03:03.175 --> 03:08.743
But you know, Catholic interpretation has long seen her as an evocation of the Blessed Mother.

03:09.464 --> 03:16.754
The 12 stars in her head where there's the 12 tribes of Israel because she kind of sums up the longing of Israel.

03:17.154 --> 03:20.620
And this interpretation is given strength by what follows.

03:20.720 --> 03:27.050
Listen, she was pregnant and crying out in birth pangs in the agony of giving birth.

03:27.952 --> 03:32.679
So here's Mary, the mother of God, about to give birth.

03:33.020 --> 03:34.002
What are we talking about here?

03:34.182 --> 03:44.018
But Christmas, not in an austerely metaphysical way, not through historical narrative, but through this kind of strange apocalyptic symbolism.

03:44.770 --> 03:51.800
You know, you might say it's looking at the Christmas story from the highest vantage point, from the vantage point of God.

03:51.840 --> 03:53.903
How does God see what's happening?

03:54.564 --> 03:58.490
So the woman about to give birth, but now here's what I want you to focus on.

03:58.510 --> 04:08.886
Now listen, another portent appeared in heaven, a great red dragon with seven heads and 10 horns.

04:10.728 --> 04:14.674
The dragon stood before the woman who was about to bear a child,

04:15.074 --> 04:19.518
so that he might devour her child as soon as it is born."

04:20.419 --> 04:20.679
Wow.

04:21.620 --> 04:25.804
That's a very powerful frightening image, isn't it?

04:25.824 --> 04:27.766
Mary, the mother of God, about to give birth.

04:27.786 --> 04:29.067
You think, well, how wonderful.

04:29.127 --> 04:31.870
The son of God is being born into the world.

04:32.430 --> 04:35.654
Angels will sing, the shepherds will visit, the little drummer boy will come.

04:35.714 --> 04:37.635
What a wonderful, wonderful moment.

04:37.655 --> 04:38.837
Yeah, true enough.

04:39.397 --> 04:44.562
But when we squint at this scene through the lens of

04:45.538 --> 04:48.221
in apocalyptic imagination, what do we see?

04:48.241 --> 04:55.528
That from the beginning, the birth of this child is opposed.

04:57.630 --> 05:13.106
By forces we can see, but behind them, and this is so typical of the Bible, both Old Testament and New, behind those forces we can see, there's an unseen force of malevolence.

05:14.018 --> 05:17.622
There's the enemy of the human race to give him his ancient name.

05:19.003 --> 05:23.088
The one who stands opposed to God's intentions.

05:23.628 --> 05:26.772
The dragon about to devour the child.

05:27.513 --> 05:35.021
That's the great dark power that is opposed to God's entry into the world.

05:35.141 --> 05:36.963
Does that make sense?

05:36.983 --> 05:42.109
Now, does he have, as I suggest, lots of visible minions around?

05:43.050 --> 05:43.410
Yeah.

05:43.778 --> 05:45.320
Lots of them, lots of them.

05:46.042 --> 05:48.265
But he's the power behind all of them.

05:49.046 --> 05:53.173
And he's the one who stands opposed to the Son of God.

05:53.954 --> 06:00.965
You know, with that in mind, by the way, take a look back at Luke's more familiar Christmas story.

06:01.005 --> 06:05.171
And you'll see it's not just a nice little tale you tell to kids.

06:06.033 --> 06:06.734
How's it begin?

06:06.814 --> 06:09.458
Well, one of the dragon's minions

06:09.890 --> 06:13.896
Caesar Augustus, the emperor of the whole world, calls for a census.

06:14.637 --> 06:17.782
He's expressing his domineering power over the world.

06:18.103 --> 06:23.491
Because of that, Mary and Joseph were chased out of their home and they got to make their way to Bethlehem.

06:24.112 --> 06:28.278
When they seek shelter, so Mary can give birth, they are turned away.

06:28.338 --> 06:32.985
The baby is wrapped in swaddling clothes.

06:33.005 --> 06:34.968
Well, see, the church fathers didn't miss this.

06:35.609 --> 06:38.674
They saw the swaddling clothes around the baby.

06:39.266 --> 06:47.118
as evocative of the burial clause that will wrap his dead body some 30 years later after it comes down from the cross.

06:48.179 --> 06:53.527
He's placed in the manger, the place where the animals eat because of the climax of his life.

06:54.028 --> 06:57.112
He'll be offered as his body and blood.

06:58.154 --> 06:59.676
His blood poured out on the cross.

06:59.716 --> 07:03.862
His body offered on the cross will be presented as food for the world.

07:04.483 --> 07:09.010
The point is there are overtones and echoes

07:09.474 --> 07:14.240
of the opposition to Christ from the beginning.

07:15.141 --> 07:17.244
And they come throughout that story.

07:18.385 --> 07:25.894
Revelation's account of the red dragon states it very bluntly and clearly, but you can see it echoed elsewhere.

07:27.697 --> 07:31.241
Now, are we meant to be discouraged by all this?

07:31.762 --> 07:32.803
No, no.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.626
And again, the book of Revelation is our key.

07:37.308 --> 07:38.610
The child we hear

07:38.690 --> 07:48.060
is born and then immediately is snatched away from the dragon and brought up to reign on a throne in the presence of God.

07:48.841 --> 07:49.863
What's the point everybody?

07:51.184 --> 07:53.306
Yes, Christ was opposed.

07:53.887 --> 07:54.868
Listen now.

07:54.888 --> 07:59.633
Yes, Christ being born in us will be opposed.

08:00.194 --> 08:01.736
Don't be surprised by that.

08:01.976 --> 08:02.857
Expect it.

08:04.078 --> 08:07.282
That when Christ, the Christ child as it were,

08:07.874 --> 08:09.116
is born in you.

08:10.037 --> 08:15.026
When you're being transformed, see, into Christ, expect opposition.

08:16.568 --> 08:30.611
But that child, that Kingly child, is more powerful than anything that's in the world, is more powerful even than the great dragon that threatens him.

08:32.153 --> 08:35.218
Listen to this now as the book of Revelation account goes on.

08:36.514 --> 08:38.417
War broke out in heaven.

08:39.219 --> 08:44.227
Michael and his angels fought against the dragon and the angels fought back and they were defeated.

08:45.069 --> 08:45.670
There it is.

08:45.730 --> 08:48.154
It's such a liberating message.

08:49.176 --> 08:52.261
The war breaks out between the spiritual powers, good and evil.

08:54.545 --> 09:02.098
The good forces are led by this baby king and they win the victory.

09:03.490 --> 09:13.083
That's the confidence everybody we should have, the confidence we should have in the spiritual power that can overcome anything that opposes Christ being born in us.

09:14.185 --> 09:14.545
Okay?

09:15.086 --> 09:19.652
Now, with that in mind, that's that great book of Revelation Christmas story.

09:20.253 --> 09:26.642
With that in mind, let's look at the gospel for today, this Feast of the Holy Family.

09:28.642 --> 09:41.536
When the Magi had departed, behold, the angel of the Lord, there's one of the good angels, appeared to Joseph in a dream and said, rise, take the child and his mother, fleet Egypt, stay there until I tell you, why?

09:42.177 --> 09:47.243
Because Herod is going to search for the child to destroy him.

09:48.044 --> 09:55.792
Now, link this everybody, link this passage to what we just heard from the moment of his birth.

09:55.852 --> 09:57.234
There's this great dragon.

09:57.602 --> 10:02.668
symbolic of the dark power, the dark and visible power, the enemy of the human race.

10:03.609 --> 10:09.056
As I've been saying, that power has minions throughout the world.

10:09.196 --> 10:10.698
Caesar Augustus being one of them.

10:12.721 --> 10:23.474
And here we see one of his nastier minions, Herod, this pathetic figure, spending his whole life clinging to power.

10:25.090 --> 10:29.577
destroying his enemies, even his own family, putting his own sons to death.

10:31.400 --> 10:38.211
And he's threatened because he's heard about this, this baby king, you know, and, and this is too much.

10:38.271 --> 10:41.035
Even though he sees an old man, the end of his life, it's too much.

10:41.576 --> 10:43.399
He's got to wipe out this child.

10:44.401 --> 10:52.754
And so we know the story, this desperate, desperate horrific act where he sends his troops into Bethlehem to murder

10:53.282 --> 10:57.568
Any child under two, the mass occur of the innocence.

10:57.669 --> 11:00.473
Yeah, that's the red dragon's minion.

11:00.993 --> 11:03.818
That's the red dragon's servant.

11:07.964 --> 11:11.309
But God snatches the Christ child away from the dragon.

11:11.970 --> 11:14.213
And now listen again to this story.

11:16.757 --> 11:22.866
Joseph, wake up, take the child, Herod's after him.

11:23.266 --> 11:24.628
take the child into Egypt.

11:25.870 --> 11:33.700
And so Joseph, and again, I found so beautiful about St. Joseph, he never speaks, never once in the scripture, never speaks.

11:33.720 --> 11:35.583
He just does what he's told.

11:36.484 --> 11:42.873
He obeys the higher voice, takes the child, imagine his fear, imagine the danger of this.

11:42.893 --> 11:48.881
He knows that the king of that area is after him with the full force of his army makes his way.

11:49.041 --> 11:52.626
All travel was difficult in the ancient world, but to cross

11:52.898 --> 11:54.620
the Sinai and to get to Egypt.

11:56.262 --> 12:01.907
Joseph here is the great protector of the Christ child.

12:04.871 --> 12:15.001
I've mentioned now Christmas is about the birth of Jesus long ago, yes, but it's also about the birth of Jesus in you.

12:17.724 --> 12:19.666
Christ wants to be born in you.

12:20.418 --> 12:27.947
And maybe that life that's new spiritual life begins as something very vulnerable, like a baby.

12:27.988 --> 12:33.735
Is there a red dragon eager to devour it?

12:34.055 --> 12:35.737
Yes, there is.

12:36.558 --> 12:38.381
Count on it, bank on it.

12:39.302 --> 12:41.444
Does the red dragon have minions?

12:42.185 --> 12:46.271
Yeah, lots of them that don't want Christ flourishing in you.

12:47.933 --> 12:49.074
The good news is

12:49.218 --> 13:01.054
that God, listen, using his own minions, using his own secondary causes, finds a way to protect that Christ life in us.

13:02.376 --> 13:05.861
Can I suggest to everyone, I think it's what the church wants us to see on this feast.

13:07.924 --> 13:17.938
Be aware of St. Joseph especially, silent St. Joseph, faithful St. Joseph, listening to the higher voice,

13:18.978 --> 13:29.690
I love what Jose Maria Escriva said, that the greatest male saint in the history of the church is not a pulp or a cardinal, an archbishop, a bishop, a priest, a friar.

13:31.552 --> 13:39.741
The greatest male saint in the history of the church is a layman, is a husband, is a worker.

13:41.764 --> 13:43.986
But he's the patron of the universal church.

13:44.834 --> 13:45.555
What's his job?

13:45.936 --> 13:55.489
It was to protect the Christ child long ago, and now it is to protect the Christ's life that is being born in us.

13:57.492 --> 13:58.974
Don't be naive.

13:58.994 --> 14:00.256
The dragon is around.

14:00.656 --> 14:01.077
You bet.

14:01.778 --> 14:04.482
Don't be naive about the minions that he uses.

14:04.542 --> 14:05.363
They're everywhere.

14:06.364 --> 14:13.394
But can I urge everybody on this feast, the Holy family, this feast of the protectors of Jesus?

14:14.050 --> 14:16.253
that we look especially to Joseph.

14:18.377 --> 14:28.993
Go to Joseph, ask for his intercession, ask for his help, that he might cultivate the Christ's life in us and keep the dragon at bay.

14:30.295 --> 14:30.916
And God bless you.

14:35.844 --> 14:39.570
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron,

14:39.778 --> 14:44.946
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.

